ent, especially for models with thicker and more extended\nclouds. This work further demonstrates the importance of radiative feedback in\ncloudy atmospheric models of hot Jupiters, as this can have a significant\nimpact on interpreting spectroscopic observations of exoplanet atmospheres.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Dec 2019 21:59:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2021 23:40:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-19"}
