ngeometric theory $T$ by a generic predicate is dependent if and only if it is\n$n$-dependent for some $n$, if and only if the algebraic closure in $T$ is\ndisintegrated. An appendix by Martin Bays provides an explicit isomorphism in\nthe Kaplan-Scanlon-Wagner theorem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Dec 2019 05:02:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Jan 2020 22:20:24 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 21 Mar 2021 20:02:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-01"}
