d\nconstraints algebra and thus leads to a well-defined effective theory\nassociated with a notion of deformed covariance. Finally, we study homogeneous\nsolutions of these effective theories and, remarkably, we solve explicitly and\nin full generality the corresponding modified Einstein equations, even for the\neffective theories which do not satisfy the closeness condition.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Dec 2019 09:40:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Mar 2020 09:54:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-11"}
